This means that reverse operators (e.g. `__radd__`) won't be
hidden by the automatic wrapper that PyType_Ready produces if
the forward method exists. Although they won't work as
in Python, they will be possible to look up and call explicitly.
This should make it easier to write code that's compatible with
Cython 0.29.x and Cython 3 (where reverse operators will be
full supported).

Fixes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4750

This is a version of https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4753 that works on master (I think it's worth fixing this in both 0.29.x and master, and they need slightly different changes). It's slightly less of an issue for master though because it works with binding=True without changes

commit.message:
Mark reverse operators with METHOD_COEXIST

This means that reverse operators (e.g. `__radd__`) won't be
hidden by the automatic wrapper that PyType_Ready produces if
the forward method exists. Although they won't work as
in Python, they will be possible to look up and call explicitly.
This should make it easier to write code that's compatible with
Cython 0.29.x and Cython 3 (where reverse operators will be
full supported).

milestone.description:
Goals:
– New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
– Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
– Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
– Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
